race.comment: ZARAGOZA (4) excellent return from last on the turn when a slashing third to Sunrise over the 1000m here. Covered ground from the wide gate when a plugging sixth to Spywire over 1000m at Kembla Grange in a BM78. Back to his right level today and gets conditions to suit. Each way. ALABAMA STATE (2) raced without luck all prep and no excuses here from the inside draw. Gave away a huge start before taking good ground off Oakfield Jupiter over 1300m at Rosehill. Can hold a forward position and go close with Grima's 3kg claim. MAFIA (1) rewarded for his consistency when sat on the speed for a determined victory over 1250m at Canterbury. Stays in the calculations. IRON HAWK (3) returned from a lengthy break when taking good ground off The Blade to run second over 1300m at Rosehill. Underrated type who will be strong late. MOTOSCAFO (8) had mixed luck this time in and the tongue-tie goes on from the good gate. Will appreciate a bit of sting out of the ground and not to be underestimated.
